{"title":"Cyclist’s Milan-San Remo predictions 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/milan-san-remo-predictions-2024","date":1710518445000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/milan-san-remo-predictions-2024\">Cyclist’s Milan-San Remo predictions 2024</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/milan-san-remo-preview\" target=\"_blank\">Milan-San Remo</a> is here again. The first <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\" target=\"_blank\">Monument</a> of 2024 and it’s going to be hotly contested. Even with Wout van Aert sitting this one out, there are a lot of riders who could really do with a big win on Via Roma.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve gathered the collective brainpower of the <em>Cyclist </em>team to make our predictions for this weekend’s race, and they’re all wholly uninspiring, but someone will probably be right considering what’s the bookies are saying.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let us know your thoughts in the comments section at the bottom.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Pete Muir, editor: Mads Pedersen</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen-970x485.jpeg\" alt=\"cyclist in Lidl-Trek kit riding an e-bike in front of his teammates and fans\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen-970x485.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen-300x150.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen-768x384.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen-1536x768.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen-360x180.jpeg 360w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen-750x375.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen-1140x570.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/lidl-trek-mads-pedersen.jpeg 1600w\" /><figcaption>Lidl-Trek</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As usual, it will come down to who can attack on the Poggio. Mathieu van der Poel will be marking <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tadej-pogacar-greatest-of-all-time\" target=\"_blank\">Tadej Pogačar</a>. Pogačar will be marking Van der Poel. Mads Pedersen will get the jump on both of them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And I say that as someone who has never been wrong in a race prediction.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Will Strickson, website editor: Filippo Ganna</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-970x646.jpeg\" alt=\"ganna_hour_record_win\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-1536x1023.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win-350x233.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/10/07125628/ganna_hour_record_win.jpeg 1600w\" /><figcaption>Ineos Grenadiers</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Filippo Ganna outsprinted Tadej Pogačar and Wout van Aert for second last year, in a year he was focussed on battering the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/filippo-ganna-hour-record\" target=\"_blank\">Hour record</a>. Everyone will be anticipating Van der Poel, so it’s either going to be someone completely rogue or Ganna, and I couldn’t vote against that face.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Robyn Davidson, editorial assistant: Mathieu van der Poel</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-970x647.jpeg\" alt=\"mathieu van der poel winning milan-san remo 2023\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/03/Mathieu-van-der-Poel-wins-2023-Milan-San-Remo-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption>Milan-San Remo</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I’ll go for a three-man break featuring Pedersen and someone like Christophe Laporte. Van der Poel will go two in a row and win with a bike throw.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Martin James, production editor: Tadej Pogačar</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Tadej Pogačar winning Strade Bianche 2024\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Strade-Bianche-Race-Gallery-043-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>James York</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, it’s hardly deep insight to choose (arguably) the best cyclist in the world right now as the most likely to win, but come on, He told everyone where he was going to attack at <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/strade-bianche-gallery-2024\" target=\"_blank\">Strade Bianche</a> ahead of time, did exactly that, and still won at a canter. That’s a degree of superiority, plus a touch of elite-level shithousery, that you can only admire. Not that I’m expecting him to win with an 81km solo break like he did in Tuscany, because Milan-San Remo is a very different kind of race and even he’s not capable of that… is he? </p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/milan-san-remo-preview-favourites\">Who are the favourites for Milan-San Remo 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/watch-milan-san-remo\">How to watch Milan-San Remo 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/milan-san-remo-preview\">Milan-San Remo 2024: Route, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n            